file.content:
components:
  schemas:
    tmp0:
      properties:
        id: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp1:
      properties:
        status_code: {type: string}
        status_message: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp2:
      properties:
        status_code: {type: string}
        status_message: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp3:
      properties:
        comment: {type: string}
        entries_action: {type: string}
        entries_domain: {type: string}
        entries_id: {type: string}
        entries_obj_seq: {type: string}
        entries_status: {type: string}
        entries_type: {type: string}
        id: {type: string}
        name: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp4:
      properties:
        allow-routing: {type: string}
        associated-interface: {type: string}
        color: {type: string}
        comment: {type: string}
        dynamic_mapping: {type: string}
        end-mac: {type: string}
        list: {type: string}
        name: {type: string}
        organization: {type: string}
        policy-group: {type: string}
        sdn-addr-type: {type: string}
        start-mac: {type: string}
        subnet: {type: string}
        subnet-name: {type: string}
        tagging: {type: string}
        type: {type: string}
        uuid: {type: string}
        visibility: {type: string}
      type: object
  securitySchemes:
    BasicAuth: {scheme: basic, type: http}
info:
  contact: {email: frikky@shuffler.io, name: '@frikkylikeme', url: 'https://twitter.com/frikkylikeme'}
  description: Automated generation of Fortinet Fortimanager
  title: Fortinet Fortimanager
  version: 1.0.0
  x-logo: data:image/png;base64,
openapi: 3.0.2
paths:
  tmp0:
    post:
      description: Add a domain filter in FortiManager to block a host or domain
      parameters:
      - description: CSV string of domains or IPs or Hosts to block
        example: downloadavirus.com,123.123.123.123
        in: query
        name: Domain CSV
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Comment to add to the filter
        example: this filter does x
        in: query
        name: Comment
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Filter name
        example: ''
        in: query
        name: Filter Name
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp0'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: FortiManager Block Domain or Host
  tmp1:
    post:
      description: FortiManager block a file Hash
      parameters:
      - description: Uploaded file to block in the FortiManager firewall. If not provided,
          must provide file hash, name and length
        example: ''
        in: query
        name: File To Block
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: CRC32 Hash (signed) of the file to block. Only needed if 'File
          To Block' isn't uploaded
        example: '2362324337'
        in: query
        name: File CRC32 Hash Value
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Name of the file to block. Only needed if 'File To Block' isn't
          uploaded
        example: myfile.exe
        in: query
        name: File Name
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Length of the file content (in bytes) to block. Only needed if
          'File To Block' isn't uploaded
        example: '854'
        in: body
        name: File Length
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Unique name to tag the entry with. Cannot be set in conjunction
          with Randomize Tag
        example: MyNewTag
        in: query
        name: Rule Tag Name
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Randomly generate a tag name. Cannot be used if Rule Tag Name
          is set
        example: ''
        in: query
        name: Randomize Tag
        required: true
        schema: {type: boolean}
      - description: Comment to add to the entry
        example: Block virus.exe
        in: query
        name: Comment
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp1'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: FortiManager Block Hash
  tmp2:
    post:
      description: FortiManager block an IP
      parameters:
      - description: Enable/disable use of this address in the static route configuration.
        example: ''
        in: query
        name: Allow Routing
        required: true
        schema: {type: boolean}
      - description: Name of the entry
        example: ''
        in: query
        name: Entry Name
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Entry type to block, see README for a full list
        example: iprange
        in: query
        name: Entry Type
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Network interface associated with this address. Defaults to 'any'
        example: any
        in: query
        name: Interface
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: If blocking an IP range, this is the start IP of the range
        example: 192.168.1.5
        in: query
        name: Start IP
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: If blocking an IP range, this is the end IP of the range
        example: 192.168.1.9
        in: query
        name: End IP
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Gateway of the entry
        example: 192.168.1.0
        in: query
        name: Subnet Gateway
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Gateway of the entry
        example: 255.255.255.0
        in: query
        name: Subnet Mask
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp2'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: FortiManager Block IP
  tmp3:
    post:
      description: List domain filters or get domain filter in FortiManager
      parameters:
      - description: ID of a domain filter to get information about. If unset, will
          return all
        example: '1'
        in: body
        name: Domain ID
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp3'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: FortiManager Get Domain Filters
  tmp4:
    post:
      description: Get all entries or single entry in FortiManager
      parameters:
      - description: Address to look up in the firewall. If not specified, will return
          all firewall entries
        example: FIREWALL_AUTH_PORTAL_ADDRESS
        in: query
        name: Address
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp4'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: FortiManager Get Firewall Entry
tags:
- {name: Network Security & Management}
